.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/13--memory-quality-and-indexing/25-indexing-runtime-bootstrap-api.md:24:**Index-scope invariants (Packet 026/005):** file collection is governed by the shared path-policy module `mcp_server/lib/utils/index-scope.ts`. Its `shouldIndexForMemory()`, `shouldIndexForCodeGraph()`, and `isIndexableConstitutionalMemoryPath()` predicates permanently exclude `z_future/` and `/external/` subtrees across memory discovery, spec-doc classification, parser admissibility, code-graph recursive scanning, and storage-layer tier mutation surfaces. `resolveCanonicalPath()` hardens the exclusion check against symlink escapes before policy evaluation. The constitutional tier is restricted to real rule files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/` — the constitutional `README.md` stays excluded per ADR-005 and storage-boundary remediation. Defense-in-depth runs at save time: `memory-save.ts` rejects excluded paths with `E_MEMORY_INDEX_SCOPE_EXCLUDED` and downgrades non-indexable constitutional `importanceTier: constitutional` to `important` before persistence, recording a `tier_downgrade_non_constitutional_path` row in the governance audit. Walker DoS caps surface structured `warnings` and `capExceeded` fields. Operator maintenance for pre-existing pollution lives in `scripts/dist/memory/cleanup-index-scope-violations.js` (`--apply` / `--verify`); verify counts should be `constitutional_total=2`, `z_future_rows=0`, `external_rows=0`, `invalid_constitutional_rows=0`.
