.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.0.1.3.md:77:The MMR (Maximal Marginal Relevance) diversity reranker needs the vector embeddings of each result to compute pairwise similarity. But the vector search channel had already retrieved these embeddings moments earlier. MMR was fetching them again from the database, one by one, using a linear scan (`reranked.find()`) to match results. The vector search channel now passes its retrieved embeddings forward in a request-scoped cache. MMR checks the cache first and only queries the database for any embeddings that weren't already retrieved. The linear the find helper lookup was replaced with a Map for O(1) access.
